Mask/Subnet Mask/Network Mask
  - a value to divide IP address to 2 parts
    - network address
    - host address
  - defines network-host address boudary
  - always begins with a contiguous block of 1's
  - allow host to send traffic to host on same subnet via switches.
    otherwise, router.
  - local router = default gateway
  - isSameSubnet = source IP === dst IP
  - 32bits long, dotted decimal/slash notation

Host address
  - must be unique, no all 0's or 1's
  - must be 1 to 254
